ates primarily reflect the American public's profound divisions and ambivalence toward freedom of speech and the legitimacy of liberal secular democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aIslam and politicszUnited States. 0aIslamxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aIslamophobiazUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh1 aBulliet, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDelogu, C. Jon1 aHillenbrand, Carole1 aMarzouki, Nadia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRoy, Olivier08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066255908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook Package 2017z978311065472108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017z978311054330808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2017z9783110548242oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/marz1768040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231543927423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231543927.jpg  a978-3-11-054330-8  CUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2017b2017  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-065472-1  CUP eBook Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066255-9  CUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZD